step_data.thought:
I've already searched for New York City and the map is now showing New York City. The Map Layers panel is already open as indicated by the heading 'Map Layers' [207] in the accessibility tree. Now I need to explore the different map layers available.

Looking at the list items under the Map Layers heading, I can see there are four different map styles available:
1. Standard [228] - This is likely the default map style
2. CyclOSM [246] - This appears to be a cycling-focused map style
3. ÖPNVKarte [264] - This is probably a public transportation focused map style (ÖPNV is German for public transport)
4. Humanitarian [282] - This is likely a style focused on humanitarian aid/disaster response

Let me click on the CyclOSM option to see how the map changes with this layer.
